---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { LegalLinks } from "../components/auth/LegalLinks";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - Home Planner">
  <div class="flex min-h-screen flex-col">
    <main class="flex-1">
      <section class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8">
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl text-foreground">
              Terms of Service
            </h1>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground">
              Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                By accessing or using Home Planner ("the Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you disagree with any part of these terms, you may not access the Service.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">2. Description of Service</h2>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                Home Planner is a web-based family calendar application that helps families coordinate schedules, manage events, and synchronize with external calendar services. The Service allows you to create and manage family calendars, connect external calendars (Google Calendar and Microsoft 365), and coordinate schedules among family members.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">3. User Accounts</h2>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">3.1. Account Creation</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                  You must create an account using Google Sign-in to use the Service. You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account and for all activities that occur under your account.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">3.2. Family Administration</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                  The user who creates a family becomes the "Admin" and has full control over the family group, including the ability to invite members, manage child profiles, and remove members. All adult members have permission to create and manage events for all family members.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">3.3. Account Responsibility</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                  You are responsible for all activities that occur under your account. You must immediately notify us of any unauthorized use of your account.
                </p>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">4. Acceptable Use</h2>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <p class="text-muted-foreground">You agree not to:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
                  <li>Use the Service for any illegal purpose or in violation of any laws</li>
                  <li>Violate or infringe upon the rights of others</li>
                  <li>Transmit any harmful, offensive, or inappropriate content</li>
                  <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Service or other users' accounts</li>
                  <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service or servers</li>
                  <li>Use automated systems to access the Service without permission</li>
                  <li>Share your account credentials with others</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">5. External Calendar Integration</h2>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">5.1. Read-Only Access</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                  The Service provides read-only synchronization with external calendars. Events from external calendars cannot be edited or deleted within Home Planner. To modify external calendar events, you must use the original calendar service.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">5.2. OAuth Permissions</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                  By connecting an external calendar, you grant Home Planner permission to read your calendar data through OAuth 2.0. You can revoke this permission at any time by disconnecting the calendar in your settings or through your Google/Microsoft account settings.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">5.3. Calendar Provider Terms</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                  Your use of external calendar services is also subject to the terms and conditions of those providers (Google Calendar Terms of Service and Microsoft Services Agreement).
                </p>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">6. Content and Data</h2>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">6.1. Your Content</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                  You retain ownership of all content and data you create within Home Planner. By using the Service, you grant us a license to store, process, and display your content as necessary to provide the Service.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">6.2. Family Data Sharing</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                  All data you create in Home Planner is shared with members of your family group. By adding content to the Service, you consent to sharing that content with your family members.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">6.3. Data Deletion</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                  You can delete your account and associated data at any time. Deletion is permanent and cannot be undone. When you delete your account, all events and data associated with your account will be removed.
                </p>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">7. Service Availability</h2>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                We strive to provide reliable service but do not guarantee that the Service will be available at all times. The Service may be unavailable due to maintenance, updates, or unforeseen circumstances. We are not liable for any loss or damage resulting from Service unavailability.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                To the maximum extent permitted by law, Home Planner and its providers shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits or revenues, whether incurred directly or indirectly, or any loss of data, use, goodwill, or other intangible losses resulting from your use of the Service.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">9. Changes to Terms</h2>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. We will notify users of any material changes by posting the updated Terms on this page and updating the "Last updated" date. Your continued use of the Service after such changes constitutes acceptance of the new Terms.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">10. Termination</h2>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                We may terminate or suspend your account and access to the Service immediately, without prior notice, for any reason, including breach of these Terms. You may terminate your account at any time by deleting it through the Service settings.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">11. Contact Information</h2>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                If you have any questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us through the application or your preferred method of communication.
              </p>
            </section>
          </div>

          <div class="pt-8 border-t">
            <LegalLinks client:load />
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>

